# golden + per-kernel snapshots are regenerable from fixtures/ via capture/ -- not tracked
data/
# fixtures/ (frozen problem definitions: static data + inputs) are heavy -- large.pt is 115 MB,
# over GitHub's 100 MB limit -- so they are NOT tracked on the remote. They are transported
# out-of-band (scp to the cluster /bucket). Kept locally on disk for capture/ + experiments.
fixtures/
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.egg-info/
.pytest_cache/
# nsys/ncu profiling outputs -- regenerable, large; kept locally, not tracked
experiments/profiles/
# LaTeX build intermediates (regenerable via latexmk) -- keep .tex/.bib/.pdf, drop the rest
paper/*.aux
paper/*.bbl
paper/*.blg
paper/*.fdb_latexmk
paper/*.fls
paper/*.log
paper/*.out
paper/*.synctex.gz
